FBIS3-55357 "drsov005_t_94012" FBIS-SOV-94-005 Document Type:Daily Report 7 Jan 1994 BALTIC STATES Estonia Decree Issued To Battle Corruption in Armed Forces WS0601181194 Tallinn ETA NEWS BULLETIN in English 0738 GMT 6 Jan 94 WS0601181194 Tallinn ETA NEWS BULLETIN Language: English Article Type:BFN [From 6 January PAEVALEHT, p 3] [Text] Thursday, January 6 -- Commander-in-chief of the Defence Forces General Aleksander Einseln issued a decree yesterday on prevention of corruption in the Armed Forces, head of the Defence Forces Chancellery Mart Tiru announced. General Einseln based the decree on his experience in the U.S. Army and the analogical U.S. code, since no regulations determining corruption or unethical behaviour existed so far in the Estonian Defence Forces. The decree bans, among other things, exploitation of official position for personal gain and the making of decisions exceeding the limits of authority.
